Unit Overview

This unit examined industry and enterprise security standards and their role in guiding risk assessment and mitigation.

Artefacts

Wiki contribution mapping standards to industries

Framework comparison notes

Individual Contribution

I analysed applicable frameworks for different organisational contexts and contributed recommendations to the module wiki.

Reflection

This unit demonstrated how standards translate risk theory into operational controls. I learned that while compliance does not guarantee security, standards such as ISO 27001 and ISO 31000 provide a critical baseline for governance, accountability, and continuous improvement.

